I would like you to implement a module named TopModule with the following
interface. All input and output ports are one bit unless otherwise
specified.

 - input clk
 - input in       (8 bits)
 - output anyedge (8 bits)

Implement a module that for each bit in an 8-bit input vector, detect
when the input signal changes from one clock cycle to the next (detect
any edge). The output bit of anyedge should be set to 1 the cycle 
after the input bit has 0 to 1 or 1 to 0 transition occurs. Assume all 
sequential logic is triggered on the positive edge of the clock.


[2026-05-14 11:09:23,336 - mage.agent - INFO] Initial rtl:
[2026-05-14 11:09:23,337 - mage.agent - INFO] module TopModule (
    input logic clk,
    input logic [7:0] in,
    output logic [7:0] anyedge
);

    logic [7:0] prev_in;
    logic [7:0] curr_in;
    logic [7:0] edge_detected;
    logic [7:0] delayed_edge;

    // Initialize previous inputs to avoid X
    initial begin
        prev_in = 8'b0;
        curr_in = 8'b0;
    end

    // Sequential logic: track current and previous input
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        prev_in <= curr_in;
        curr_in <= in;
    end

    // Combinational edge detection (XOR each bit)
    assign edge_detected = curr_in ^ prev_in;

    // Delay the edge detection by one cycle
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        delayed_edge <= edge_detected;
    end

    // Output assignment
    assign anyedge = delayed_edge;

endmodule
